- cs.OC (Optimization and Control) is also likely as the paper discusses dynamic programming, which is a common optimization technique.
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is another possible category as the paper deals with Boolean functions and graph theory.
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is a possible category as the paper compares the time complexity of the proposed algorithm to a deterministic one.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper uses quantum computing techniques, which are often used in machine learning.
